cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new architecture for LTE-5G integration and evaluates its performance through simulations.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper may involve information theory concepts in evaluating the performance of the proposed architecture.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with mmWave cellular networks, which are used for high-speed multimedia applications.
- cs.AR (Augmented Reality) is a possible category as the paper may involve the use of 5G networks for augmented reality applications.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon security aspects of the proposed architecture.
